      "comment_id" : 101768450,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@parsecer: Because SortedMap is a specialication of Map, which returns a Set, since there is no order and the information that each element is unique is more valuable. You can (most likely) cast (or transform) that <code>Set</code> in a <code>SortedSet</code>, where you have a <code>first()</code> again. You can also use <code>SortedMap.firstKey()</code> for that."
