    "body" : "<p><code>LinkedHashMap</code> maintains the order of the keys.</p>\n<p><code>java.util.LinkedHashMap</code> appears to work just like a normal <code>HashMap</code> otherwise.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 9359310,
      "reputation" : 4173,
      "user_id" : 7245145,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Avc0HA8J.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Steffi Keran Rani J",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7245145/steffi-keran-rani-j"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1538998571,
    "creation_date" : 1538998571,
    "answer_id" : 52701395,
    "question_id" : 663374,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have used <strong>Simple Hash map, linked list and Collections</strong> to sort a Map by values.</p>\n\n<pre><code>import java.util.*;\nimport java.util.Map.*;\npublic class Solution {\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        // create a simple hash map and insert some key-value pairs into it\n        Map&lt;String, Integer&gt; map = new HashMap&lt;String, Integer&gt;();\n        map.put(\"Python\", 3);\n        map.put(\"C\", 0);\n        map.put(\"JavaScript\", 4);\n        map.put(\"C++\", 1);\n        map.put(\"Golang\", 5);\n        map.put(\"Java\", 2);\n        // Create a linked list from the above map entries\n        List&lt;Entry&lt;String, Integer&gt;&gt; list = new LinkedList&lt;Entry&lt;String, Integer&gt;&gt;(map.entrySet());\n        // sort the linked list using Collections.sort()\n        Collections.sort(list, new Comparator&lt;Entry&lt;String, Integer&gt;&gt;(){\n        @Override\n         public int compare(Entry&lt;String, Integer&gt; m1, Entry&lt;String, Integer&gt; m2) {\n        return m1.getValue().compareTo(m2.getValue());\n        }\n      });\n      for(Entry&lt;String, Integer&gt; value: list) {\n         System.out.println(value);\n     }\n   }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The output is:</p>\n\n<pre><code>C=0\nC++=1\nJava=2\nPython=3\nJavaScript=4\nGolang=5\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
