  "title" : "Java Ordered Map",
  "body" : "<p>Is there an object in Java that acts like a Map for storing and accessing key/value pairs, but can return an ordered list of keys and an ordered list of values, such that the key and value lists are in the same order?</p>\n<p>So as explanation-by-code, I'm looking for something that behaves like my fictitious OrderedMap:</p>\n<pre><code>OrderedMap&lt;Integer, String&gt; om = new OrderedMap&lt;&gt;();\nom.put(0, &quot;Zero&quot;);\nom.put(7, &quot;Seven&quot;);\n\nString o = om.get(7); // o is &quot;Seven&quot;\nList&lt;Integer&gt; keys = om.getKeys();\nList&lt;String&gt; values = om.getValues();\n\nfor(int i = 0; i &lt; keys.size(); i++)\n{\n    Integer key = keys.get(i);\n    String value = values.get(i);\n    Assert(om.get(key) == value);\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
